    "answer_id" : 79658447,
    "question_id" : 2591083,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since Java 10, use:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>int required = 21;\nint feature = Runtime.version().feature();\nif (feature &lt; required) {\n    throw new IllegalStateException(String.format(&quot;Java version is %d, required %d&quot;, feature, required));\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p><code>Runtime.version().major()</code> is deprecated</p>\n<p><sub>Stolen from a <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2591083/getting-java-version-at-runtime/79658447#comment114024309_45417933\">comment</a> by <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/7178314/fidekild\">@fidekild</a></sub></p>\n"
